<h3 align="center"><b><u>School Closure Update</u></b></h3>
<br><p>Thursday, April 23</p>
							<p>Dear Bonner Families:</p>
							<p>Yesterday Governor Bullock held a press conference at which he announced that, while he will permit schools to open as early as May 7th, the decision of whether to reopen schools is up to local school boards.  For Bonner School, the decision of whether or when to reopen school will be made by our Board of Trustees at a Special Board Meeting, to be held next Wednesday, April 29th, at 7:00 PM.  If you are interested in watching or providing input at that meeting, the agenda as well as details on how to connect online will be posted here on our school website by Monday afternoon, April 27th.</p>
							<p>There is much for our trustees to consider as they weigh this decision, and of highest priority in their deliberations will be the health and safety of our students, families and school personnel. Before Bonner School were to reopen, we must determine how we would enforce ongoing social distancing requirements and health precautions in a school setting. There are no simple answers as to how we would achieve this in our full classrooms, cafeteria, playgrounds and on our school buses.</p>
							<p>For the time being, Bonner School personnel will continue to deliver meals and distance learning packets in the same way as we have the past weeks, and teachers will continue connecting with students to support their learning. We will do our best to keep you informed of any changes as they occur.  Feel free to contact me at 258-6151 or <a href="mailto:jhoward@bonner.k12.mt.us?Subject=Bonner%20School%20Closure">jhoward@bonner.k12.mt.us</a> if you have questions or concerns.</p>
							<p>Sincerely:</p>
<br><p>Jim Howard,</p>
							<p>Superintendent</p>
<hr>
<p>Click the <a href="documents/toh.pdf">staff link</a> for teacher's email contact information and office hours.  General questions can be emailed to our Secretary at <a href="mailto:hlopuch@bonner.k12.mt.us?Subject=Bonner%School%20Question">hlopuch@bonner.k12.mt.us</a>. Homework questions can be emailed directly to teachers.</p>
<hr>
